                <head>339. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>United States interest in the scientific exploration of outer space during the
                    mid and late 1950’s was part of a broader concern with the military value of
                    outer space exploration, including the use of extraterrestrial military
                    reconnaissance and intelligence gathering satellite vehicles, and ballistic
                    missile and anti-missile research and development.</p>
            </div>
